<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The memcpy uses pp->xbuf_pos as the length but there is no runtime check that pp->xbuf_pos <= sizeof(pp->xbuf). The function only asserts (pp->xbuf_pos < sizeof(xbuf)), which does not guarantee the source buffer pp->xbuf is large enough. If sizeof(pp->xbuf) is smaller than sizeof(xbuf) (or pp->xbuf_pos has been corrupted/incorrectly set) and pp->xbuf_pos exceeds sizeof(pp->xbuf), memcpy(xbuf, pp->xbuf, pp->xbuf_pos) will read beyond the bounds of pp->xbuf (out-of-bounds source access).
</scenario>

